OL,3,CPolice officers committed gross
OL,4,Cmisconduct when arrested man died in
OL,5,Cpolice van
OL,7,FPC Hunkin described Mr Reardon as
OL,8,F"playing games" when seeing him
OL,9,Fshaking and unresponsive through the
OL,10,Fvan's Perspex divide.
OL,12,FThe IOPC found that Mr Reardon's name
OL,13,Fwas called out by the officers 63
OL,14,Ftimes during the journey to custody.
OL,16,FHowever, despite him not responding
OL,17,Fand spending 22 minutes on the van
OL,18,Ffloor, they failed to stop and assess
OL,19,Fhis condition.
