OL,3,CPolice officers committed gross
OL,4,Cmisconduct when arrested man died in
OL,5,Cpolice van
OL,7,FPC MacKenzie had argued that, as he
OL,8,Fwas driving the van, responsibility
OL,9,Ffor monitoring Mr Reardon fell to his
OL,10,Fjunior colleague. However, the panel
OL,11,Fdeemed both officers had joint
OL,12,Fresponsibility and should have offered
OL,13,Fearly medical assistance to Mr Reardon.
OL,15,FA police misconduct hearing in Exeter
OL,16,Fconcluded on Thursday 14 August that
OL,17,Fthe officers had committed gross
OL,18,Fmisconduct. They were found in breach
OL,19,Fof the duties and responsibilities
OL,20,Fstandard of professional behaviour.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
