OL,5,Cpolice van
OL,7,FHe added: "None of the attending
OL,8,Fofficers seemed to take responsibility
OL,9,Ffor Mr Reardon's supervision and he
OL,10,Fwas not thoroughly searched.
OL,12,F"And we found no evidence of
OL,13,Fdiscussions over moving the handcuffs
OL,14,Ffrom the front to the rear in line
OL,15,Fwith local and national policy. It
OL,16,Fmeant Mr Reardon was able to put a
OL,17,Fpackage into his mouth, undetected,
OL,18,Fbefore the journey began.
